alternative_parents.description: Compounds containing a sulfoxide functional group, with the structure RS(=O)R' (R,R' not H).
alternative_parents.name: Sulfoxides

alternative_parents.description: Organic compounds containing a sulfinyl group with the general formula RS(=O)R' (R = organyl, R' = any atom but O).
alternative_parents.name: Sulfinyl compounds

alternative_parents.description: Organic compounds containing an oxide group.
alternative_parents.name: Organic oxides

alternative_parents.description: Derivatives of hydrocarbons obtained by substituting one or more carbon atoms by an heteroatom. They contain at least one carbon atom and heteroatom.
alternative_parents.name: Hydrocarbon derivatives

class.description: Aromatic compounds containing one monocyclic ring system consisting of benzene.
class.name: Benzene and substituted derivatives

description: This compound belongs to the class of organic compounds known as benzyl alkyl sulfoxides. These are organosulfur compounds that contain a sulfoxide group substituted by a benzyl group, and an alkyl group. They have the general structure RS(=O)R' ( R=benzyl, R'=alkyl).

direct_parent.description: Organosulfur compounds that contain a sulfoxide group substituted by a benzyl group, and an alkyl group. They have the general structure RS(=O)R' ( R=benzyl, R'=alkyl).
direct_parent.name: Benzyl alkyl sulfoxides

kingdom.description: Compounds that contain at least one carbon atom, excluding isocyanide/cyanide and their non-hydrocarbyl derivatives, thiophosgene, carbon diselenide, carbon monosulfide, carbon disulfide, carbon subsulfide, carbon monoxide, carbon dioxide, Carbon suboxide, and dicarbon monoxide.
kingdom.name: Organic compounds

subclass.description: Organosulfur compounds that contain a sulfoxide group substituted by a benzyl group. They have the general structure RS(=O)R' ( R=benzyl, R'=organyl).
subclass.name: Benzyl sulfoxides

superclass.description: Aromatic compounds containing one or more benzene rings.
superclass.name: Benzenoids
